~=~=~=~=~
|| MBF ||
~=~=~=~=~
   mbf is a modified implementation of the esoteric programming language Brainfuck (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brainfuck), with the addition of macros along with it.

`mbf` stands for "macro brainfuck".

~=~=~=~=~=~=~=~=~=~=~=~=~=
|| USAGE -- HELLO WORLD ||
~=~=~=~=~=~=~=~=~=~=~=~=~=
   ###################
   # hello_world.mbf #
   ###################

   # hello macro
   hello {
      > 8+ [< 9+ > -] < .
      > 4+ [< 7+ > -] > +.
      7+ . .
      3+ .
      >> 6+ [< 7+ >-] < ++.
      12- .
      > 6+ [< 9+ >-] < + .
      <.
      3+ .
      6- .
      8- .
      >>> 4+ [< 8+ >-] <+ .
   }

   # call hello
   hello;

   #########
   # SHELL #
   #########
   
   % # use mbf -h for help
   
   % mbf ./hello_world.mbf
   Hello, World!

   % mbf -E expanded.bf hello_world.mbf
   [SUCCESS] file was successfully written!
   
   % cat expanded.bf
   >++++++++[<+++++++++>-]<.>++++[<+++++++>-]<+.+++++++..+++.>>++++++[<+++++++>-]<++.------------.>++++++[<+++++++++>-]<+.<.+++.------.--------.>>>++++[<++++++++>-]<+.

~=~=~=~=~=~=~=
|| FEATURES ||
~=~=~=~=~=~=~=
o   Strict superset of BF
o   100% compatible with ordinary BF
o   Includes an interpreter to execute MBF/BF code
o   Lets you know when you make a syntax error
o   Supports comments
o   Macros can call another macros
o   Insensitive to whitespaces/indentation
o   Lets you save the compiled BF code
o   Includes =-h=/=--help= option for help

~=~=~=~=~=~=~=
|| EXAMPLES ||
~=~=~=~=~=~=~=
   You may find more examples in `example/` directory.

